tiles.name: Credential Result Messages Processed by IPV Core
Markdown
tiles.markdown: *A Credential Result message is written to an SQS queue consumed by IPV Core once ID Check's processing completes. It will contain a verifiable credential if no errors occurred, or an error message otherwise.*

tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown: *Note: VCs Issued and Journeys Started are not paired in this data, so it is possible to see percentages above 100 in time periods where more VCs were issued than new journeys started.*

tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown: *To see production-only data, use the filter in the top right to select the `di-mobile-id-check-async-prod` management zone.*

tiles.name: Age of Oldest Message on DLQ
Markdown
tiles.markdown:
*Messages that repeatedly fail to be processed by IPV Core are sent to the DLQ (Dead Letter Queue). Its SQS queue name is
`mob-async-backend-ipv-core-outbound-dlq`.*
